  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd 3 \u0bae\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc1\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Power outage for 3 hours from tomorrow",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka (PUCSL) has given permission to the Ceylon Electricity Board (CEB) to implement a three-hour power cut from Monday to July 3 in view of the fuel crisis.",
        "In zones A to W, power cuts will be implemented for 40 minutes during the day and 1 hour and 20 minutes at night.",
        "C.C. The zones will be without electricity for 2 hours from 6 am to 8 am, except on July 2 and 3.",
        "It is noteworthy that the Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka has given permission to the Electricity Board to implement power cuts in M, N, O, X, Y, Z Zones from 5 am to 8 am for 3 hours."
      ],
